üìù Challenge Description

"You're going to prison kid. There's no way around that. Take a good look and learn your betters. Your life will depend on them now. This ain't no scandinavian heaven where you're handed everything on a silver platter."

üìÅ Provided File:

üö© Flag Format: Either CTF{server_host(ChunkX,ChunkY,ChunkZ)} (case insensitive and ascii characters only) - Careful, these are chunk coordinates, not block coordinates. Or if you don't have a Minecraft account: CTF{server_host:owner_username}

üìã Example: CTF{mc.hypixel.net(-69,420,10)} or CTF{mc.hypixel.net:hypixel}

üîç Initial Exploration

The challenge provided a Minecraft screenshot titled "prison.png" showing several players in what appears to be a prison environment. The description hinted at identifying the server and potentially its owner.

üïµÔ∏è First Observations:

  • üéÆ Minecraft server screenshot with multiple players
  • üë• Player names visible in the chat and above characters
  • üîñ One player has an "own-" tag prefix
  • üè¢ Prison-themed Minecraft environment
  • üéØ Need to identify server host and/or owner username

Since this was an OSINT challenge, my first approach was to analyze the image for any identifiable information about the players and server.

üõ†Ô∏è Investigation Process

üîé Step 1: Player Identification

I carefully examined the prison.png image and noted the visible player names and characteristics:

Visible players: - Player on far right with "own-" tag prefix - Partial name visible: "leaky_" - Distinctive skin pattern on the suspected owner

The player on the far right with the "own-" tag was particularly interesting, as this likely indicated they were the server owner or had special privileges.

üìö Step 2: Minecraft Player Research

Using the partial name "leaky_" and the distinctive skin, I turned to NameMC, a popular Minecraft username and skin database:

https://namemc.com

Searching for players beginning with "leaky_*", I found a user named "Leaky_Tandos" who matched the skin pattern visible in the screenshot.

üí° Key Discovery: The player with the "own-" tag was likely Leaky_Tandos, based on the skin match and name pattern.

üåê Step 3: Server Identification

With a potential owner username identified, I searched for servers associated with Leaky_Tandos:

Google search: "Leaky_Tandos" server

This search led me to a Minecraft forum post where Leaky_Tandos was promoting their server:

https://miecraftforum.net

On this forum, I found a post by Leaky_Tandos advertising their prison server:

Server address: play.thepen-mc.net Server type: Prison Owner: Leaky_Tandos

üîç Critical Insight: The server name "thepen-mc.net" perfectly matched the prison theme of the challenge, confirming we had found the correct server.

üéØ Step 4: Flag Construction

With both the server host and owner username identified, I could construct the flag according to the specified format:

Format: CTF{server_host:owner_username} Values: server_host = play.thepen-mc.net owner_username = Leaky_Tandos

This gave us the final flag:

üö© ctf{play.thepen-mc.net:Leaky_Tandos}
